e. Aluminum Ore explores the often overlooked history of bauxite in the twentieth century, and in doing so examines the forces that shaped the time, from the mineral's strategic development in the First World War and throughout the Cold War, to its role in the globalization of markets, as companies from the northern hemisphere vied for the resources of the south. In this wide-ranging collection, scholars from around the world consider multiple international perspectives on this history -- from Guinea to Nazi Germany to Jamaica -- all while examining the central place of one commodity in a time of change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAluminum mines and miningxEnvironmental aspects. 0aAluminum mines and miningxHistory. 0aAluminum mines and miningxPolitical aspects. 0aAluminum mines and miningxSocial aspects. 0aGlobalizationxEconomic aspects. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Economy.2bisacsh1 aBarclay, Lou Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCampbell, Bonnie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCross, Bradley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDas, Samarendra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFortescue, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrøland, Hans Otto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGendron, Robin S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGendron, Robin S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGirvan, Norman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHove, Jon Olav, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIngulstad, Mats, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relat